The '''Furniture Museum''' ({{lang-no|Møbelmuseet}}), formerly known as the ''Norsk Møbelfaglig Senter'' 'Norwegian Furniture Design Center',<ref>{{cite web|title=Norsk Møbelfaglig Senter - Furniture Design Centre|url=http://kulturarv.no/en/node/517|website=Norsk kulturarv|accessdate=January 31, 2018}}</ref> is a museum and documentation center for the furniture industry in [[Norway]]. The museum is located in [[Aure, Sykkylven|Aure]] in the municipality of [[Sykkylven]],<ref name="Sunnmore">{{cite web|title=Furniture Museum, Sykkylven|url=http://www.sunnmore.museum.no/english/furniture-museum/|website=Stiftinga Sunnmøre Museum|accessdate=January 31, 2018}}</ref> and it is part of the [[Sunnmøre Museum Foundation]].<ref name="Sunnmore"/><ref>{{cite web|last1=Hjemdahl|first1=Anne-Sofie|title=Stiftelsen Sunnmøre museum|url=https://snl.no/Stiftelsen_Sunnm%C3%B8re_museum|website=Store norske leksikon|accessdate=January 31, 2018}}</ref> The museum has a permanent display presenting the history of the furniture industry.
